The paper deals with online learning, which is a subfield of machine learning, and involves analyzing the performance of algorithms in the presence of uncertainty. The use of probabilistic graphs as feedback is a key feature of the paper, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory) due to the focus on graph-based feedback.
